## File Modification Rules

### When adding new API endpoints:
1. Create route in `backend/app/routers/` with `/api/{resource}` prefix
2. Register router in `backend/app/main.py`
3. Add corresponding API function in `frontend/src/lib/api.js`
4. Add i18n keys in both `frontend/src/locales/tr.json` and `frontend/src/locales/en.json`

### When adding new database models:
1. Create model in `backend/app/models/` inheriting from `Base`
2. Import model in `backend/app/database.py` `init_db()` function
3. Add migration SQL in `init_db()` for new columns (use `IF NOT EXISTS` pattern)
4. Do NOT use Alembic for migrations — project uses manual SQL migrations in `init_db()`

### When modifying broadcast logic:
1. Changes go in `backend/app/services/broadcast_service.py`
2. Respect the queue pattern — only one broadcast runs at a time
3. Always handle `TelegramRetryAfter`, `TelegramForbiddenError`, `TelegramBadRequest` exceptions
4. Update `_active_broadcasts` dict for progress tracking
5. Log all significant events with Turkish messages

### When modifying frontend pages:
1. Use inline styles matching the dark theme (`#070b18` background, indigo/purple accents)
2. Use `useTranslation()` hook for all user-facing text
3. Use `api.js` functions for all HTTP requests — never call axios directly
4. Handle loading/error states in components
5. Use `react-hot-toast` for user notifications

### When working with the Telegram Bot:
1. Always use `get_bot()` from `bot_service` — never instantiate Bot directly
2. Bot uses HTML parse mode by default
3. Fresh router must be created on each bot start (see `create_router()`)
4. Bot polling runs as an `asyncio.Task` — be careful with cancellation
5. `send_notification()` silently fails if bot is not running

---

## Testing Notes

- No test framework is currently configured
- When adding tests, prefer `pytest` with `pytest-asyncio` for backend
- Use `httpx.AsyncClient` with `ASGITransport` for FastAPI endpoint testing
- Mock aiogram Bot in tests — never call real Telegram API in tests

---

## Environment Variables

| Variable | Default | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `POSTGRES_USER` | `tgbot` | PostgreSQL username |
| `POSTGRES_PASSWORD` | `tgbot_secret` | PostgreSQL password |
| `POSTGRES_DB` | `tgbot` | PostgreSQL database name |
| `SECRET_KEY` | `changeme_super_secret_key_32chars` | JWT signing key (min 32 chars) |
| `ADMIN_USERNAME` | `admin` | Panel login username |
| `ADMIN_PASSWORD` | `admin123` | Panel login password |
| `UPLOAD_DIR` | `/app/uploads` | File upload directory |
| `DOMAIN` | — | Deployment domain |
